import spark.implicits._
import org.apache.spark.sql._// import Column type

def dollarsToEuros(c: Column): Column = c * 0.9
val interpolatedColumns3 = df02.select($"Id", $"SalePrice" as "Sale Price in Dollar", dollarsToEuros($"SalePrice") as "Sale Price in Euros")// notice the String Interpolation
z.show(interpolatedColumns3)

## Statistical operations

msg.data: Statistical operations

paragraphs.text:
/**
 * Notice the $ sign for Column interpolation <- there is no $ sign in the tutorial!!! 
 * The complaint was around the renaming operator "as"
 */
val stats = df02.select(
    variance($"SalePrice") as "Variance",
    mean($"SalePrice" as "Mean"),
    stddev($"SalePrice" as "Standard Devisation")
    )

z.show(stats)
